The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, August 09, 2004 				 Bollywood boy joins pizza parade
				 	 Zayed Khan: New role																								New Delhi, Aug. 8 (PTI): After signing up Cindy Crawford and Pamela Anderson, Pizza Hut is hiring Bollywoods Zayed Khan as its brand ambassador to reach out to the youth.																								We have hired a brand ambassador for the first time in India. Our idea is to cater to the younger generation of the young country, Pankaj Batra of the worlds biggest pizza chain said. But he declined to reveal any detail about the contract.																								Pizza Hut will soon increase the number of its food joints in India from 73 outlets in 19 cities to 100 restaurants in 26 cities.																								With the fast-food industry in the country touching about Rs 98,000 crore, the company views India as a critical market because of its sheer size, Batra said.																								Pizza Hut will be one of the first few brands being endorsed by Khan, whose claim to fame is Bollywood blockbuster Main Hoon Na.																								The Bollywood star has, apart from Crawford and Anderson, boxing legend Mohammad Ali and former President Mikhail Gorbachev for company. 
